result.execSummary:
The defendant Stephanie M Schmidlkofer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take >$500 - $5000), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Stephanie M Schmidlkofer in court with attorney M E Weathers.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern, Lucas Bennewitz, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Counts 1 and 2,  Court finds defendant guilty.

Court orders the following:

Count 1:
- Sentence withheld.  Credit for 58 days if revoked.
- 3 years Probation.  Court would allow for early termination of Probation after 2 years if all conditions have been met.
- Court costs of $278.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- DNA Surcharge waived.
- Restitution of $1,474.93 to be paid as a Condition of Probation as follows:  $1,039.93 to Target; $435 to Benedon's
- Conditions of Probation:  Continue with AODA treatment/counseling.  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Valid prescriptions to be taken in the manner they were prescribed.  Attend a minimum of 2 self help meetings per week and obtain a sponsor within a month.  Maintain full-time employment and/or school.  No contact with Target Stores or with Benedon's.

Count 2:
- 9 months Huber with standard release conditions. STAYED.  Credit for 58 days if revoked.
- 1 year Probation. 
- Court costs of $243.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- DNA Surcharge waived
- Conditions of Probation: Same as Count 1.
